SIMPLE: precisian
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Precisian
<hw>Pre*ci"sian</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One
who limits, or restrains.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An overprecise person; one rigidly or ceremoniously
exact in the observance of rules; a formalist; -- formerly applied to
the English Puritans.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The most dissolute cavaliers stood aghast at the dissoluteness of
the emancipated <qex>precisian</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Precisianism</ent>⟦br⟧
